args: Hello, Elias. I didn't know you were here.\nIt's nice to see you.
Would you care for some tea?
Hey, if it isn't Elias! What brings you here?
Er, something wrong? You seem mad.

If you aren't mad, you're doing a poor job
of being happy. You have been frowning
since you walked in the door, and we're
having to pry conversation out of you.
Did something happen, Elias?\nWhy have you come here, anyway?
Lucretia, please take me with you on your\nnext tour!
I want to study with you.
Well, you DO yet have much to learn.\nHowever...
I want to study singing more than anything.
So please take me with you!
Er, but then why did you come here?
She told me to come to your castle\nand have lots of different experiences.
I want to be just like her. Is that so bad?
Nah. Just kind of adorable, is all.
H-hey! ...Anyway, is it all right if I stay\nhere for a while?
...Yo, Elias! There ya are. It's chowtime.
I don't need food—what I NEED is to\npractice my singing.

Practice is all well and good, kid,
but if ya don't eat, yer gonna get
all weak and spindly. Gotta keep
yer strength up, yeah?
Pfft. I don't need strength like yours.
Hey, I'm just lookin' out for ya!\nNo need for the attitude.
Ugh, this is becoming a distraction.\nI'm going to practice somewhere else,\nso don't follow me!
...So yeah, didn't have any luck pinnin'\nhim down today, either.
It's been several days since Elias came to\nthe Halidom, and he's yet to take a single\nmeal with the rest of us.
Kid's head is full of nothin' but notes\nand lyrics, if you ask me.
He does seem quite focused—almost to\nthe point of obsession.
I imagine he's trying his best to take\nLucretia's dismissal in stride.
That kid's puttin' way too much pressure on\nhimself. He's got plenty'a time to make his\nway in the world, yeah?
He does seem to break for meals by\nhimself on occasion, but I worry he\nisn't eating enough.
I'll take some food to his room.
He'll eat, even if I have to force him.
I followed the music exactly, but...
Urgh. You could at least knock if you're\ngoing to come into my room, Prince.
I did knock. A lot, actually.
Anyway, here. I brought you some food.\nYou haven't eaten much today, have you?
This is no time for me to stuff my face.
I'm not telling you to gorge yourself,\nbut if you don't eat SOMETHING,\nyou're going to get sick.
The path of the singer is a harsh one,\nbut I've made up my mind to pursue\nit no matter what may come.
And to do that, I must practice and study\nharder than anyone else.
You see? Your body's trying to tell you\nthat it needs to eat.
If you keep pushing yourself, you might\nend up not being able to sing at all.
What's the big hurry with all of this,\nanyway?
I want to be the best singer I can be,\nso there's no time for sitting on my\nlaurels and letting life pass me by.
That's also why I wanted to go\nwith Lucretia.
But wasn't she the one who told you to\ncome to the Halidom and have a lot of\ndifferent experiences?
Then maybe you should do that.
She knows what matters to you;\nshe wouldn't have made that\nsuggestion for no reason at all.
Very well. I'll try it your way.
Great! Then your first experience should\nbe to eat this plate of food.
